<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="271" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,150,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,150,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="271">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[870,1022,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="271">longihamatus</emphasis>
, referring to the clavate dorsoapical process of the sacculus in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
